OL,6,FThe parents of a woman from Exeter who
OL,7,Fdied from ME have questioned why she
OL,8,Fwasn't kept in hospital after she was
OL,9,Fadmitted with severe symptoms.
OL,11,FMaeve Boothby O'Neill died at her home
OL,12,Fin October 2021, aged 27. The daughter
OL,13,Fof Times journalist Sean O'Neill, had
OL,14,Fmyalgic encephalomyelitis (ME).
OL,16,FAlso called chronic fatigue syndrome,
OL,17,FME is a long-term condition that can
OL,18,Faffect different parts of the body.
