OL,3,CDoctor had 'never seen' ME patient
OL,4,Cwith such severe symptoms, inquest told
OL,6,FAccording to NHS England its cause is
OL,7,Funknown, but the most common symptom
OL,8,Fis extreme tiredness.
OL,10,FDr Thomas Fox, a consultant
OL,11,Fendocrinologist and physician at the
OL,12,FRoyal Devon and Exeter Hospital, saw
OL,13,FMaeve in March of 2021.
OL,15,FHe told the inquest that, although she
OL,16,Fappeared weak, there was no medical
OL,17,Freason at the time to admit her.
OL,19,FShe was capable of drinking with
OL,20,Fminimal assistance and consuming
OL,21,Fmashed or liquified food, he explained.
