OL,3,CDoctor had 'never seen' ME patient
OL,4,Cwith such severe symptoms, inquest told
OL,6,FHe said he recognised it as a real
OL,7,Fcondition, but there was uncertainty
OL,8,Famong experts about its causes and he
OL,9,Fhad not been given any specific
OL,10,Ftraining in how to treat it.
OL,12,FIn his acute medicine role, he had a
OL,13,Fsmall amount of knowledge about a lot
OL,14,Fof things.
OL,16,FHe added that, like many of the other
OL,17,Fdoctors, he'd never seen an ME patient
OL,18,Fwith such severe symptoms.
